The paper focuses on language generation using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of training GANs for language generation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new regularization term for WGANs, which is related to optimization and algorithms, falling under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper compares the performance of different approaches for training GANs for language generation, which involves image processing techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
